\section{Introduction}

\href{https://monopoly.hasbro.com/en-us}{Monopoly} has served as a prime source of entertainment for both children and adults all around the world. The decisions one is required to make and the significant risk factors make Monopoly one of the most attractive games to humans as shown in \href{https://mashable.com/2015/01/21/monopoly-facts/#:~:text=The}{this third party evidence.}
\\
\\
This overwhelming popularity has allowed for the Parker Brothers to further innovate Monopoly even making it \href{https://monopoly.hasbro.com/en-us}{playable online by cooperating with Hasbro}.
\\
\
\hrule

\section{Rule Improvements}

\subsection{Passing Through Go}
\begin{itemize}
\item When a player with more than \$500 passes go, they may not collect \$200.
\\
\item When a player with less than \$500 passes go, only \$100 may be collected. 
\\
\end{itemize}

To sum it up, it would look like such:
\\


\[
    \$ \text{ at Go}= 
\begin{cases}\
    \$100, & \text{if Player > \$ 500} \\
     \$0,              & \text{if Player < \$ 500}
\end{cases}
\]


\
\subsection{Renting Modifications}
\begin{itemize}
    \item If rentee has two ownership cards of the same color, rent price increases 50\%.
    \item If rentee has all ownership cards of the same color, rent price increases 100\%. 

\end{itemize}
\subsubsection{Other Changes}
\begin{itemize}
    \item Triple the cost of rent universally
    \item Double the cost of landing on railroads and utilities 
\item Half the cost of houses and hotels

\end{itemize}

\textbf{In other Words:}

\begin{table}[h!]
\centering
\begin{tabular}{l|r}
Two Cards & All Cards \\\hline

\(x \times 1.5\) & \(x \times 2\)
\end{tabular}

\caption{\label{tab:widgets}Renting Value : X = Standard Rent Price}
\end{table}

\subsection{Strategic Movements (Strants)}
\begin{itemize}
    \item Each player is given 6 number cards (1,2,3,4,5,6)
    \item Along with one role of a dice, the player must add the number displayed on a card.
    \item The player must not repeat the card until all cards are used.

\end{itemize}

